The issue in useProfileData.ts is at line 39 where it's setting `dayMaster` to a string, but the new BaziData type expects an object. I need to update the fetchBaziSummary function to return the new format, or make the dayMaster optional and use legacy fields.

Looking at the BaziData type I defined:
```typescript
export interface BaziData {
  dayMaster?: {
    element: string;
    character: string;
    description: string;
  };
  fiveElements?: Record<string, number>;
  dailyFortune?: string;
  // Legacy support
  pattern?: string;
  fortuneLevel?: 1 | 2 | 3 | 4 | 5;
  todayFortune?: string;
}
```

The BaziSummaryCard handles the legacy format by checking if `dayMaster` exists as an object or falling back to pattern. So I need to update useProfileData to not set `dayMaster` as a string, but rather leave it undefined and use the legacy `pattern` field instead (since that's what the API returns).

